Schema Definitions

PEER-GROUP-ERROR-HANDLING-STATE:

PEER GROUP ERROR HANDLING STATE

treat-as-withdraw: boolean

Specify whether erroneous UPDATE messages for which the NLRI can be extracted are reated as though the NLRI is withdrawn - avoiding session reset

Example
{
  "treat-as-withdraw": "boolean"
}

AFI-SAFI-IPV6-LABELED-UNICAST:

AFI SAFI IPV6 LABELED UNICAST

prefix-limit: AFI-SAFI-IPV6-LABELED-UNICAST-PREFIX-LIMIT

Configure the maximum number of prefixes that will be accepted from a peer

Example
{
  "prefix-limit": {
    "state": {
      "shutdown-threshold-pct": "integer",
      "prevent-teardown": "boolean",
      "restart-timer": "string",
      "max-prefixes": "integer"
    }
  }
}

AFI-SAFI-USE-MULTIPLE-PATHS-EBGP-STATE:

AFI SAFI USE MULTIPLE PATHS EBGP STATE

allow-multiple-as: boolean

Allow multipath to use paths from different neighbouring ASes

Example
{
  "allow-multiple-as": "boolean"
}

CONFEDERATION-STATE:

CONFEDERATION STATE

member-a: integer[]
identifier: integer

enabled: boolean

Example

  "member-a": [
    "integer"
  ],
  "identifier": "integer",
  "enabled": "boolean"
}

  "state": {
    "maximum-paths": "integer"
  }
}

AFI SAFIS AFI SAFI APPLY POLICY STATE

export-policy: string[]
import-policy: string[]
default-import-policy: string accept-route, reject-route

explicitly set a default policy if no policy definition in the import policy chain is satisfied

default-export-policy: string accept-route, reject-route

explicitly set a default policy if no policy definition in the export policy chain is satisfied

Example

  "export-policy": [
    "string"
  ],

AFI-SAFI-L3VPN-IPV6-MULTICAST-PREFIX-LIMIT-STATE:

AFI SAFI L3VPN IPV6 MULTICAST PREFIX LIMIT STATE

shutdown-threshold-pct: integer

Threshold on number of prefixes that can be received from a neighbour before generation of warning messages or log entries

prevent-teardown: boolean

Do not tear down the BGP session when the maximum prefix limit is exceeded, but rather only log a warning

restart-timer: string

Time interval in seconds after which the BGP session is re-established after being torn down due to exceeding the max-prefix limit

max-prefixes: integer

Maximum number of prefixes that will be accepted from the neighbour

Example
{
  "shutdown-threshold-pct": "integer",
  "prevent-teardown": "boolean",
  "restart-timer": "string",
  "max-prefixes": "integer"
}

TRANSPORT-STATE:

TRANSPORT STATE

local-address: string

Set the local IP (either IPv4 or IPv6) address to use for the session when sending BGP update messages

local-port: integer

Local TCP port being used for the TCP session supporting the BGP session

tcp-mss: integer

Sets the max segment size for BGP TCP sessions

remote-port: integer

Remote port being used by the peer for the TCP session supporting the BGP session

passive-mode: boolean

Wait for peers to issue requests to open a BGP session, rather than initiating sessions from the local router

remote-address: string

Remote address to which the BGP session has been established

mtu-discovery: boolean

Turns path mtu discovery for BGP TCP sessions on (true) or off (false)

Example
{
  "local-address": "string",
  "local-port": "integer",
  "tcp-mss": "integer",
  "remote-port": "integer",
  "passive-mode": "boolean",
  "remote-address": "string",
  "mtu-discovery": "boolean"
}

AFI-SAFIS-AFI-SAFI-ROUTE-SELECTION-OPTIONS-STATE:

AFI SAFIS AFI SAFI ROUTE SELECTION OPTIONS STATE

enable-aigp: boolean

Flag to enable sending / receiving accumulated IGP attribute in routing updates

ignore-as-path-length: boolean

Ignore the AS path length when selecting the best path

advertise-inactive-routes: boolean

Advertise inactive routes to external peers

ignore-next-hop-igp-metric: boolean

Ignore the IGP metric to the next-hop when calculating BGP best-path

always-compare-med: boolean

Compare multi-exit discriminator (MED) value from different ASes when selecting the best route

external-compare-router-id: boolean

When comparing similar routes received from external BGP peers, use the router-id as a criterion to select the active path

Example
{
  "enable-aigp": "boolean",
  "ignore-as-path-length": "boolean",
  "advertise-inactive-routes": "boolean",
  "ignore-next-hop-igp-metric": "boolean",
  "always-compare-med": "boolean",
  "external-compare-router-id": "boolean"
}

OVERLAY-OCNI-BPM-NEIGHBOR-STATE:

State information relating to the BGP neighbor

send-community: string standard, extended, both, none

Specify which types of community should be sent to the neighbor or group

neighbor-address: string

Address of the BGP peer, either in IPv4 or IPv6

local-as: integer

The local autonomous system number that is to be used when establishing sessions with the remote peer or peer group, if this differs from the global BGP router autonomous system number

description: string

An optional textual description (intended primarily for use with a peer or group

route-flap-damping: boolean

Enable route flap damping

session-state: string idle, connect, active, opensent, openconfirm, established

Operational state of the BGP peer

enabled: boolean

Whether the BGP peer is enabled

peer-as: integer

AS number of the peer

peer-group: string

The peer-group with which this neighbor is associated

remove-private-as: string

Remove private AS numbers from updates sent to peers - when this leaf is not specified, the AS_PATH attribute should be sent to the peer unchanged

auth-password: string

Configures an MD5 authentication password for use with neighboring devices

supported-capability: string[]
peer-type: string internal, external

Explicitly designate the peer or peer group as internal (iBGP) or external (eBGP)

established-transitions: integer

Number of transitions to the Established state for the neighbor session

last-established: integer

This timestamp indicates the time that the BGP session last transitioned in or out of the Established state

Example
{
  "send-community": "string",
  "neighbor-address": "string",
  "local-as": "integer",
  "description": "string",
  "route-flap-damping": "boolean",
  "session-state": "string",
  "enabled": "boolean",
  "peer-as": "integer",
  "peer-group": "string",
  "remove-private-as": "string",
  "auth-password": "string",
  "supported-capability": [
    "string"
  ],
  "peer-type": "string",
  "established-transitions": "integer",
  "last-established": "integer"
}

ROUTE-SELECTION-OPTIONS-STATE:

ROUTE SELECTION OPTIONS STATE

enable-aigp: boolean

Flag to enable sending / receiving accumulated IGP attribute in routing updates

ignore-as-path-length: boolean

Ignore the AS path length when selecting the best path

advertise-inactive-routes: boolean

Advertise inactive routes to external peers

ignore-next-hop-igp-metric: boolean

Ignore the IGP metric to the next-hop when calculating BGP best-path

always-compare-med: boolean

Compare multi-exit discriminator (MED) value from different ASes when selecting the best route

external-compare-router-id: boolean

When comparing similar routes received from external BGP peers, use the router-id as a criterion to select the active path

Example
{
  "enable-aigp": "boolean",
  "ignore-as-path-length": "boolean",
  "advertise-inactive-routes": "boolean",
  "ignore-next-hop-igp-metric": "boolean",
  "always-compare-med": "boolean",
  "external-compare-router-id": "boolean"
}

max-prefixes: integer

Maximum number of prefixes that will be accepted from the neighbour

PEER-GROUP-TRANSPORT-STATE:

PEER GROUP TRANSPORT STATE

tcp-mss: integer

Sets the max segment size for BGP TCP sessions

Set the local IP (either IPv4 or IPv6) address to use for the session when sending BGP update messages

mtu-discovery: boolean

Turns path mtu discovery for BGP TCP sessions on (true) or off (false)

passive-mode: boolean

Wait for peers to issue requests to open a BGP session, rather than initiating sessions from the local router

Example

NEIGHBOR-GRACEFUL-RESTART-STATE:

NEIGHBOR GRACEFUL RESTART STATE

peer-restart-time: integer

The period of time (advertised by the peer) that the peer expects a restart of a BGP session to take

enabled: boolean

Enable or disable the graceful-restart capability

stale-routes-time: string

An upper-bound on the time thate stale routes will be retained by a router after a session is restarted

peer-restarting: boolean

This flag indicates whether the remote neighbor is currently in the process of restarting, and hence received routes are currently stale

helper-only: boolean

Enable graceful-restart in helper mode only

local-restarting: boolean

This flag indicates whether the local neighbor is currently restarting

restart-time: integer

Estimated time (in seconds) for the local BGP speaker to restart a session

mode: string helper-only, bilateral, remote-helper

Ths leaf indicates the mode of operation of BGP graceful restart with the peer

Example
{
  "peer-restart-time": "integer",
  "enabled": "boolean",
  "stale-routes-time": "string",
  "peer-restarting": "boolean",
  "helper-only": "boolean",
  "local-restarting": "boolean",
  "restart-time": "integer",
  "mode": "string"
}

PEER-GROUP-TIMERS-STATE:

PEER GROUP TIMERS STATE

connect-retry: string

Time interval in seconds between attempts to establish a session with the peer

keepalive-interval: string

Time interval in seconds between transmission of keepalive messages to the neighbor

minimum-advertisement-interval: string

Minimum time which must elapse between subsequent UPDATE messages relating to a common set of NLRI being transmitted to a peer

hold-time: string

Time interval in seconds that a BGP session will be considered active in the absence of keepalive or other messages from the peer

Example
{
  "connect-retry": "string",
  "keepalive-interval": "string",
  "minimum-advertisement-interval": "string",
  "hold-time": "string"
}

OVERLAY-OCNI-BPM-PEER-GROUP-STATE:

State information relating to the BGP peer-group

send-community: string standard, extended, both, none

Specify which types of community should be sent to the neighbor or group

local-as: integer

The local autonomous system number that is to be used when establishing sessions with the remote peer or peer group, if this differs from the global BGP router autonomous system number

peer-group-name: string

Name of the BGP peer-group

route-flap-damping: boolean

Enable route flap damping

peer-as: integer

AS number of the peer

remove-private-as: string

Remove private AS numbers from updates sent to peers - when this leaf is not specified, the AS_PATH attribute should be sent to the peer unchanged

auth-password: string

Configures an MD5 authentication password for use with neighboring devices

peer-type: string internal, external

Explicitly designate the peer or peer group as internal (iBGP) or external (eBGP)

total-prefixes: integer

Total number of BGP prefixes received within the context

total-paths: integer

Total number of BGP paths within the context

description: string

An optional textual description (intended primarily for use with a peer or group

Example
{
  "send-community": "string",
  "local-as": "integer",
  "peer-group-name": "string",
  "route-flap-damping": "boolean",
  "peer-as": "integer",
  "remove-private-as": "string",

AFI-SAFI-ROUTE-SELECTION-OPTIONS-STATE:

AFI SAFI ROUTE SELECTION OPTIONS STATE

enable-aigp: boolean

Flag to enable sending / receiving accumulated IGP attribute in routing updates

ignore-as-path-length: boolean

Ignore the AS path length when selecting the best path

advertise-inactive-routes: boolean

Advertise inactive routes to external peers

ignore-next-hop-igp-metric: boolean

Ignore the IGP metric to the next-hop when calculating BGP best-path

always-compare-med: boolean

Compare multi-exit discriminator (MED) value from different ASes when selecting the best route

external-compare-router-id: boolean

When comparing similar routes received from external BGP peers, use the router-id as a criterion to select the active path

Example
{
  "enable-aigp": "boolean",
  "ignore-as-path-length": "boolean",

      "l3vpn-ipv4-unicast": {
        "prefix-limit": {
          "state": {
            "shutdown-threshold-pct": "integer",
            "prevent-teardown": "boolean",

}

peer-groups-afi-safi_schema:

    OVERLAY-OCNI-BPM-PEER-GROUP-AFI-SAFIS-AFI-SAFI
afi-safi-name: string

Reference to the AFI-SAFI name used as a key for the AFI-SAFI list
